While testing snapshot code changes for EUCA-13186, my cloud's eucalyptus-cloud process running the Storage Controller connected to the "temp" Ceph cluster in the EQS lab crashed.

[~shaon] notes that this is not as beefy a Ceph cluster as the regular Ceph shared cluster. Maybe it was overtaxed.

I don't think my code changes caused this, see https://github.com/eucalyptus/eucalyptus/pull/95.

It had downloaded a full snapshot from OSG and was trying to write the contents to the Ceph cluster, which had been working many times, for hours, during this test.

The test command running was:
{{~/delta_test.bash 0 1 30}}
The bash script was adapted from Casey's script of the same name, creating a snapshot and then a volume from it, then deleting a volume, in a loop. I'd removed the parts about md5 checking and attaching the volume to an instance. I'll attach it here.

The parameters mean no snapshot deltas (0) (full snaps only), one snap before each volume creation (1), and 30 snap+vol creations. So this is unrelated to snapshot deltas.

